---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Aerospace engineering student at Florida Tech. Providence, RI to Melbourne, FL.">
  <main class="about-main">

    <header class="about-header">
      <p class="label" style="color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: 1rem;">About</p>
      <h1>Systems, discipline,<br /><em>and the work before the work</em></h1>
    </header>

    <section class="about-body">
      <p>
        I grew up in Providence, Rhode Island, and graduated high school in North Attleboro, Massachusetts.
        I came to Florida Institute of Technology in Melbourne not because it was the obvious choice, but
        because it was serious about the work. Aerospace engineering. Real labs. Real hardware.
      </p>

      <p>
        I did not arrive with a background in engineering or coding. I arrived curious and willing.
        That combination has taken me further than I expected.
      </p>

      <p>
        My path has moved through rocketry, robotics, nuclear energy, and defense finance — areas that
        look scattered from the outside but are connected by one question: <em>how do complex ideas become real?</em>
        How do you take something that exists only on a whiteboard, or in a model, or in someone's head,
        and make it trustworthy enough to use in the physical world?
      </p>

      <p>
        In Panther Rocket Lab, I helped coordinate a 25+ member multidisciplinary aerospace team through
        an 8-month development cycle — structures, propulsion, avionics, ground systems, 30+ design reviews,
        a ~$10,000 project budget. I also built and launched my own high-power rocket. J-class motor.
        Blue with a gold stripe. Named Susan. Approximately 2,000 feet. Recovered after 40 minutes searching
        through brush at the Compound in Palm Bay — the beeper gave her away.
      </p>

      <p>
        In the Aerospace Systems and Propulsion Lab, I work with PhD researcher Nhut Huynh under Dr. Nguyen
        on robotics and autonomy research: ROS Noetic, Gazebo, RViz, SLAM, and data pipeline work for
        edge-AI traffic systems through SmartSignals.
      </p>

      <p>
        Independently, I have been building <strong>nuclear-pf</strong> — an open-source Python framework
        for SMR project finance modeling. My finding, preliminary: SMR competitiveness is not primarily a
        technology cost question. It is a financing structure question. The same reactor, at the same cost,
        can be financially viable or financially impossible depending entirely on what surrounds it.
      </p>

      <p>
        While all of this is happening, I work 25–30 hours a week as a Starbucks shift supervisor — promoted
        May 2026, supervising teams of up to 10, serving 300–400 customers per shift. It is not separate
        from the engineering. It is the same discipline applied to a different system under real pressure.
      </p>

      <p>
        I write because engineering without reflection can become soulless. My writing lives at
        <a href="/writing">Ground Control</a> — essays on ambition, labor, becoming, and the systems
        that hold a life together.
      </p>

      <p>
        I am first-generation. I am self-supporting. I am still figuring out most of it.
        But I have learned that the work before the work — the setup, the structure, the discipline
        before results appear — is where everything is actually decided.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="principles">
      <h2>Operating Principles</h2>
      <ul class="principles-list">
        <li><em>Build before you feel ready.</em></li>
        <li><em>Document the mess.</em></li>
        <li><em>Translate complexity.</em></li>
        <li><em>Respect physical systems.</em></li>
        <li><em>Make the invisible work visible.</em></li>
        <li><em>Discipline is not aesthetics — it is returning.</em></li>
        <li><em>Systems become real through boring work.</em></li>
        <li><em>The field notes matter.</em></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="about-quick">
      <div class="quick-grid">
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Education</span>
          <p>B.S. Aerospace Engineering<br />Florida Institute of Technology<br />Expected May 2028 · GPA 3.3</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Research</span>
          <p>Aerospace Systems and Propulsion Lab<br />ROS · Gazebo · Foxglove · MCAP<br />SmartSignals Edge-AI Traffic Systems</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Leadership</span>
          <p>Panther Rocket Lab — PM + Treasurer<br />SGA Senator<br />ANS Student Chapter — Co-Founder</p>
        </div>
        <div class="quick-item">
          <span class="label">Located</span>
          <p>Melbourne, FL<br />Originally Providence, RI</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-main {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 8rem 2rem 6rem;
  }

  .about-header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    padding-bottom: 2.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .about-header h1 em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .about-body {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .about-body p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    color: var(--dim);
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .about-body p strong { color: var(--text); }
  .about-body p em    { color: var(--text); font-style: italic; }
  .about-body p a     { color: var(--accent); }

  .principles {
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
    padding: 2.5rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .principles h2 { margin-bottom: 1.75rem; }

  .principles-list {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }

  .principles-list li {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--dim);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .principles-list li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-style: normal;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .about-quick { margin-top: 1rem; }

  .quick-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(200px, 1fr));
    gap: 2rem;
  }

  .quick-item p {
    margin-top: 0.6rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--dim);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
</style>
